This paper focuses on evaluating the cognitive load induced by different acoustic parameters for data sonification, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and signal processing (cs.SD). The study also involves examining user perceptions and EEG responses, which are related to social and information sciences (cs.SI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's findings have implications for workload management in complex systems (cs.SY).
